definitions.definition: A tricyclic aromatic hydrocarbon (an acene containing three fused rings) obtained from coal tar ; used in the manufacture of wood preservatives , insecticides and the dye alizarin ; it is isomeric with phenanthrene .

main_definition: ( organic chemistry ) A tricyclic aromatic hydrocarbon (an acene containing three fused rings) obtained from coal tar ; used in the manufacture of wood preservatives , insecticides and the dye alizarin ; it is isomeric with phenanthrene .
